newsitem.title: MALAYSIA: Malaysia rubber closes mixed on Japanese trends.
newsitem.headline: Malaysia rubber closes mixed on Japanese trends.

text.p: Malaysian rubber prices ended mixed after duly tracking Japanese futures in the continued absence of buying interest, traders said.
"Forward months in Japanese futures closed down today, that's was the only lead for the local market," said a trader.
Summer holidays in the West and buyers' reserve have suppressed regional rubber prices of late. "The mixed price is just a technical adjustment," said a dealer.
In the longer-term, regional markets may also affected by the planned sale of 60,000 tonnes of rubber by the U.S. Defence National Stockpile Centre by early 1997, traders said.
